originalQuery: Forest cover loss trends in Michigan's Upper Peninsula from 2000-2022
summary: Michigan lost 28.3 thousand hectares of natural forest in 2020, equivalent to 8.81 Mt of COâ‚‚ emissions. The state's forest coverage declined from 95% historically to 55% today, with the Upper Peninsula maintaining 84% forest cover while southern Lower Peninsula dropped to just 21%. Primary drivers include commercial logging, urban development, and agricultural expansion, particularly affecting the Hiawatha and Ottawa National Forests region.
